|dien~ = ^devono.~  Cf. the forms ^dienno~ and ^denno~,
also equivalent to ^devono.~
..TEXT:
|seme~: See ^Conv.~ IV, ii, 8: "Per che le parole, che sono
quasi seme d'operazione, si deono molto discretamente sostenere e
lasciare, perch@e bene siano ricevute e fruttifere vegnano."
("Wherefore words, which are like the seed of activities, must be very
discreetly retained and let go...in order that they may be well
received and brought to fruit.")  For the metaphor, see the parable of
the sower, especially Luc. 8: 11: "Semen est verbum Dei."  ("The seed
is the word of God.")
..TEXT:
Ugolino is referring to the wayfarer's promise
(^Inf.~ XXXII, 137-39) to "requite [him] in the world above."
