..TEXT:
|Anselmuccio mio~: The suffix -^uccio~ connotes
endearment.  Anselmuccio was the younger brother of Nino il
Brigata (vs. 89), and the two actually were grandchildren of
Ugolino, sons of his eldest son Guelfo.  Anselmuccio appears to
have been born some time after 1272, since his name is omitted
from a document of that date in which the other sons of Guelfo
are mentioned as having claims in Sardinia in their mother's
right.  Consequently he must have been about fifteen at the time
of his death.
