earth can gape enough for me").  And see Seneca, ^Thyestes~, vss.
1006-9:
..TEXT:
<<<FORMATTING-OFF>>>
     ...sustines tantum nefas gestare, Tellus? non ad infernam
     Styga tenebrasque mergis rupta et ingenti via ad chaos inane
     regna cum rege abripis?
..TEXT:
<<<FORMATTING-OFF>>>
     Canst thou endure, O Earth, to bear a crime so monstrous?
     Why dost not burst asunder and plunge thee down to the
     infernal Stygian shades and, by a huge opening to void
     chaos, snatch this kingdom with its king away?
