..TEXT:
|Gaddo~: Count Ugolino's fourth son.  The exact date
of Gaddo's birth is unknown, but he was surely a grown man by
1288.
..TEXT:
|mi si gitt@o disteso a' piedi~: We should conceive
of the prisoners as shackled.  The Pisan commentator Buti claims
to have seen the bodies "coi ferri in gamba" ("in leg-irons")
when they were removed from the tower.
