..TEXT:
|del bel paese l@a dove 'l s@i suona~: For the
traditional classification of the Romance languages according to
the affirmative adverb of each, see ^De vulg. eloqu.~ I, viii, 6:
..TEXT:
<<<FORMATTING-OFF>>>
     Totum autem quod in Europa restat ab istis, tertium tenuit
     ydioma, licet nunc tripharium videatur; nam alii ^oc~, alii
     ^o,il~, alii ^s@i~ affirmando locuntur; ut puta Yspani,
     Franci et Latini.
..TEXT:
<<<FORMATTING-OFF>>>
     But a third idiom prevailed in all that part of Europe which
     remains from the other two, though it now appears in a
     threefold form.  For of those who speak it, some say in
     affirmation ^oc~, others ^o,il~, and others ^s@i~, namely the
     Spaniards, the French, and the Italians.
