..TEXT:
|la Capraia e la Gorgona~: Two small islands in the
Mediterranean, east of the northern tip of Corsica.  Both
islands, which belonged to Pisa in Dante's time, lie fairly close
to the mouth of the Arno.  A nephew of Count Ugolino, the Count
Arselmo, took his title from Capraia.
