..TEXT:
|Branca Doria~: Member of the famous Ghibelline
house of Doria (or d'Oria) at Genoa (born ^ca.~ 1233, died ^ca.~
1325).  With the aid of a relative, either a nephew or cousin, he
treacherously murdered his father-in-law, Michel Zanche, governor
of Logudoro in Sardinia, at a banquet to which he had invited
him.  Some commentators date the murder ^ca.~ 1275, while others
prefer ^ca.~ 1290.
